               <head><title>Gesta Romanorum</title>; Grosseteste, <title>Templum dei</title></head>
               <physDesc>
                  <p><note>Comprising two originally separate MSS</note></p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>both vellum (both FSOS/<term type="disposition"
                           >FHHF</term>)</support>
                        <extent>Fols. i + 38 + i (numbered fol. 39, probably a flyleaf associated
                           with the second MS) + 8 (numbered fols. 40–7) + i (numbered fol. ii).
                              <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height quantity="268">268</height>
                              <width quantity="200">200</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1600" notAfter="1700">
                        <p>Limp vellum with two string ties to close the book, s. xvii? Sewn on four
                           thongs. At the head of the spine, ‘93’ in black ink on a paper lozenge
                           pasted on, above it ‘Gesta Romanorum’; the number also in black ink on
                           the front cover and rather indistinctly on the leading edges. Pastedowns
                           modern paper, on the front one a College bookplate. At the front, a
                           modern paper flyleaf; at the rear, a modern paper flyleaf <locus
                              from="ii" to="ii">(ii)</locus>; in addition, an old vellum flyleaf
                              <locus from="39" to="39">(fol. 39)</locus> between the two MSS.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
